16 2021-02-25 headache Headache; 16 years old received vaccine; A spontaneous report was received from a patient concerning... Read more
Close
Headache; 16 years old received vaccine; A spontaneous report was received from a patient concerning a 16-year-old female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced headache and 16 years old received vaccine. The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported. On 21-Jan-2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first dose of mRNA-1273 (lot/batch: unknown) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 23-Jan-2021, the patient experienced headache for a couple of days. Treatment for the event included ibuprofen. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. The outcome of the events, headache and 16 years old received vaccine, was considered resolved.; Reporter's Comments: This report refers to a case of product administration error  Product administered to patient of inappropriate age for mRNA-1273, lot # unknown with event of headache.Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

feeling cold; achy; feverish; they gave vaccine to my 16 year old daughter; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning her daughter, a 16-year-old female patient that received the vaccine/product delivered to a patient of inappropriate age and experienced feeling cold, feverish/pyrexia and achy/pain. The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant medications were not provided. On 09 Jan 2021, prior to the onset of symptoms, the patient received the first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: unreported) in the left arm for the prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 09 Jan 2021, the patient experienced feeling cold, feverish and achy. Treatment for these events was not provided. Caregiver inquiring as to what to do about second dose. Caregiver REFUSED permission to contact and DOES NOT want the Centers for Disease Control notified. Action taken with mRNA-1273 was not reported. The outcome of the event, received the vaccine/product delivered to a patient of inappropriate age was considered resolved. The events, experienced feeling cold, feverish/pyrexia and achy/pain, was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This report refers to a case of Product administration error  Product administered to patient of inappropriate age for mRNA-1273, lot # unknown with associated events of feeling cold, Pain ,Pyrexia .Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Pt incurred minor S/S after initial dose per the parent, low grade fever, general fatigue and malaise for approximately 24 hours. 17 2021-02-21 fatigue Hot flashes; Tired; 17-year old inadvertently given the first dose of the vaccine; A spontaneous rep... Read more
Close
Hot flashes; Tired; 17-year old inadvertently given the first dose of the vaccine; A spontaneous report was received from a parent whose 17-year-old, female daughter received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) resulting in hot flashes, and tired. The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported. On 06 Feb 2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 08 Feb 2021, the patient's father reported his daughter was given the Moderna vaccine in error as she is only 17. The patient experienced hot flashes and was tired after receiving the vaccine. No treatment information was provided. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not provided. The outcome of the event, vaccine given to a 17-year old, was considered resolved on 06 Feb 2021. The outcomes for events, hot flashes and tired, were not reported.; Reporter's Comments: This report refers to a 17-year old female patient who received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection with reported events of hot flashes and was tired. Based temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded

17 2021-03-03 fever Pt reports onset of dizziness, chest tightness, shortness of breath that started acutely 45 minutes ... Read more
Close
Pt reports onset of dizziness, chest tightness, shortness of breath that started acutely 45 minutes to 1 hour after receiving her second Moderna vaccination on 2/24/21. She reported that she was told by her employer that the symptoms were due to the Moderna vaccine. She reportedly developed fever and some throat discomfort as well. Symptoms became persistent and disrupted sleep and was unable to work. She sought medical attention in the ER for persistent symptoms on 2/26/21. Extensive workup was essentially normal. She received Zofran, Decadron, IVFs, and Albuterol inhaler while in the ER. She reported improvement in her chest tightness and SOB after Albuterol. She was discharged home with instructions to f/u with her PCP in a couple of days for recheck.
17 2021-04-20 malaise, headache Severe headache; Worst migraine; Excessive vomitting; Patient under 18 given vaccine; Hasn't felt we... Read more

Severe headache; Worst migraine; Excessive vomitting; Patient under 18 given vaccine; Hasn't felt well; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of HEADACHE (Severe headache) and VOMITING (Excessive vomitting) in a 17-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 627A21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. The patient's past medical history included No adverse event (No reported medical history). Concomitant products included DULOXETINE, CLONIDINE, HYDROXYZINE, AMITRIPTYLINE, RAMELTEON and ETHINYLESTRADIOL, NORGESTIMATE (MONO LINYAH) for an unknown indication. On 16-Mar-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 08-Mar-2021, the patient experienced MALAISE (Hasn't felt well). On 16-Mar-2021, the patient experienced PRODUCT ADMINISTERED TO PATIENT OF INAPPROPRIATE AGE (Patient under 18 given vaccine). On 08-Apr-2021, the patient experienced VOMITING (Excessive vomitting) (seriousness criterion medically significant). On 11-Apr-2021, the patient experienced HEADACHE (Severe headache) (seriousness criterion medically significant) and MIGRAINE (Worst migraine). On 08-Apr-2021, VOMITING (Excessive vomitting) had resolved. At the time of the report, HEADACHE (Severe headache), MIGRAINE (Worst migraine), PRODUCT ADMINISTERED TO PATIENT OF INAPPROPRIATE AGE (Patient under 18 given vaccine) and MALAISE (Hasn't felt well) outcome was unknown. DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): On an unknown date, White blood cell count: elevated (High) Elevated. The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown. Patient was treated with fluids, Zofran, Benadryl, Tylenol 800mg and Aspirin for headaches. Company comment: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.; Sender's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

18 2021-01-13 headache, fatigue Rash and itchiness started at around 10 PM on 1/7/2021. Rash described as "traveling across chest" a... Read more
Close
Rash and itchiness started at around 10 PM on 1/7/2021. Rash described as "traveling across chest" and similar to what happens when she takes prednisone. Stated she has not taken prednisone for over a year. Client stated that rash did not appear anywhere else on her body. Itchiness was experienced on chest and arms only. Client also stated symptoms of fatigue, muscle weakness, and "super sore arm" that lasted from day of vaccination until 1/10/2021. Client also reported a headache that lasted 2 day after vaccination. She contacted her provider on 1/7/2021 and, per provider's instruction, took 1 tablet of Benadryl. Client was unsure of dosage of Benadryl. On the morning of 1/8/2021 she took a second tablet of Benadryl and reported that her rash resolved after the second dose of Benadryl. Her itchiness resolved the morning of 1/9/2021. Stated that her Doctor did not specify a diagnosis but did state to hold off on the second dose of this vaccine.

18 2021-01-14 cough I had no pain or discomfort immediately after the shot, during the 15 minute observation period, or ... Read more
Close
I had no pain or discomfort immediately after the shot, during the 15 minute observation period, or an hour after. About 2 hours later (at 2:00 pm), I developed some hives around my neck, and the part of my arm near the injection site started to become more and more sore. I applied Benadryl to the hives and they went away. However, my left arm hurt to touch or move, much worse than any vaccine I've had before (flu, HPV). That night, I had trouble sleeping because the discomfort because of the sore left arm. I also could not sleep because of chest tightness and pressure, which worsened when lying down, but that pressure did not progress to the point of wheezing (I have asthma). Sleeping on my back was the only option because sleeping on either side was painful, which worsened the chest pressure. When I woke up, my fingers felt stiff and I had joint pain in both hands, more so in my left hand. Throughout this, I did not see any redness on my arm. This day it was agonizing to move my left arm. I could pick things up, but raising it above my the height of my waist or twisting it behind my back to get on my backpack was near impossible and was avoided. The chest pressure went away. The second night, I still had trouble sleeping, but the pain was much better, although I still could not sleep on my side. When I woke up, I had no more joint pain. That day, although the left arm was still sore, I could move it pretty well. If I made too strong of a movement, it felt like the injection site would tense up, the pain would slowly ramp up, and then diminish. That afternoon, at 4:30, I was able to play tennis with minimal soreness, and that night, I was able to sleep on my side. The following day, I had a cough, but that might have been because I didn't dress for the weather, and experiences close to zero soreness.

18 2021-02-03 throat pain, fatigue, chills, influenza like illness For my first dose, I had quite mild symptoms. I woke up with a migraine the next morning and some so... Read more
Close
For my first dose, I had quite mild symptoms. I woke up with a migraine the next morning and some soreness at the injection site. Both of these lasted a couple of days and were able to be treated with over-the-counter pain medicine. My second dose, however, provided much worse flu-like symptoms. About 12 hours after I received the injection, I was woken with a migraine much worse than the first, nausea, chills, joint pain, sore throat, and fatigue. While the chills and nausea subsided, the other symptoms persisted until the next day. As of today (2/4/21), all symptoms are gone except for soreness at the injection site.

On sunday, 05/02/2021 between the hours of 12AM to 2AM, my shortness of breath got worse to the point where I could not breathe. In general, I felt my back and chest tighten. I could only breathe (faintly) to survive. If I took any deeper breaths, my back and chest would hurt even more. As time progressed, My right neck got stiff. Then right my jaw got stiff. Then the right side of my head got stiff. Eventually, the whole right side of my body was numb -- I could move it still but it was still numb and stiff. This happened simultaneously with the breathing issues. This entire time, my whole was tensing, it felt like I could feel my veins while it rushed blood. It was terrible. I thought I was going to die. I did not know which breath would be my last, because every breath got worse and worse. I went to sleep around 2AM and I would periodically wake up. When I'd wake, the pain still persisted. It never went away. Eventually I got up to go to work around 8AM, the right side of my body wasn't as numb and the breathing wasn't as bad, but you could still tell there was an issue. This issue persisted throughout the day. As of now, these issues are not as persistent, but at least once a day, I still feel the effect. It sucks. A nurse called me (working at the urgent care I gave information about) , on 05/03/2021 saying if I was going to see a primary doctor. I told her that I have an appointment with one on 05/10/2021. She said that though they called me on 05/02/2021 towards the end of the day and told me everything was fine, that they looked a little deeper and realized that the shape of my cells were weird and that when I go to my primary doctor, they'd be able to access my information. This is of a complete shock because the shape of my cells were never weird before. This happened as a result of the covid-19 vaccine. This is reaction must be put into the VAERS system.

The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. On an unspecified date in Jan 2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received the first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: Unknown) for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On an unspecified date in Feb 2021, Patient received the second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: Unknown) for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On an unspecified date in Feb 2021, within 24 hours after receiving the second dose, patient experienced fever, hives on face/huge welts all over body, lips were swollen and obstruction breathing. The patient went to the ER and was given unspecified steriods and Diphenhydramine and the patient went to the ER (emergency room) on 19 Mar 2021 because she had another reaction and the doctor confirmed her that the vaccine triggered lupus. Close
About 3-4 hours after the injection was given, my left arm began to hurt at the sight of the injection. It was sore red and beginning to swell. After a couple more hours it was difficult to even move my arm; it felt as if my tricep was almost entirely immobilized. These symptoms persisted for about three days, with increasingly less intensity, and after the fourth day, I had no adverse symptoms. Exactly six days after receiving the vaccine, the area where the injection was given (tricep) began to feel itchy. When I tried to scratch it, the itch was not relieved but only worsened and began to swell and turn red. By the following day (7 days after injection), the site of injection and area surrounding the site of injection (about 6 inches along my upper and 3-4 inches in width) had swelled up more and was significantly more inflamed than my opposite arm which hadn't changed at all. It had a similar swelling, itch, and pain to the sensation one experiences after getting bitten by a mosquito, but in this case a very very large mosquito bite. By the evening of the seventh day, I began feeling very fatigued both mentally and physically and felt very subtle body aches that usually signal the early signs of a fever (at least for me). Upon feeling feverish symptoms I made a drink of turmeric and ginger root powder with honey and laid down for about an hour in an attempt to rest. After an hour, the body aches and fatigue lessened in intensity but my arm was still swelling and now feeling hot in temperature. The itching was unbearable. I went to go take a warm shower later that night and started to feel a mixture of pressure and pain traveling up my arm and into my chest. I began feeling my lymph nodes on the left side of my breast to find that a lymph node in my armpit and another one on the side of my breast had enlarged to about two inches in diameter. They were painful to the touch and noticeably sore when left untouched. These symptoms persisted with no change for about 2 days. After two days, the swelling and itching in my arm went away but my lymph nodes were still inflamed. They did not reduce in size or in pain until about 7 days after the first signs of these symptoms. After a week all symptoms went away.

21 2021-03-25 chills, fatigue I received an allergy immunotherapy shot the day before my first dose of the vaccine and instantly f... Read more
Close
I received an allergy immunotherapy shot the day before my first dose of the vaccine and instantly felt nauseous and extremely tired after receiving the vaccine, which continued for two days after receiving tut. Three days later, I woke up struggling to breathe (but not anaphylactic), covered in hives, itchy all over, shaking, disoriented, and chilled but not truly feverish. I reported this to my allergist, who prescribed prednisone and suggested the vaccine combined with immunotherapy were too much for my immune system for one week. The hives, itchiness, and difficulty breathing lasted about four days. I struggled with fatigue and nausea for over two weeks, stopping all school and work in the meantime. After my second dose, I feel just a bit tired and sore, so I think this truly was a bad reaction to the two injections combined rather than to the vaccine itself. Still, it was a debilitating experience, and I would recommend considering putting out guidance that other immunotherapy patients space out their allergy injections and vaccines farther than I did.

I developed Idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura (low levels of platelets) and menorrhagia due to the vaccine according to my doctor. I believe there have been about 30 cases of this occurring so far. In my case, I took the vaccine and felt relatively tired for two days. There were no other symptoms. About a week later, I got my period after not having it for a couple months. The blooding was light for a few days, but then got extremely heavy. After about a week of very heavy bleeding, I went to urgent care. They took blood tests, and found that I had a critically low level of platelets (6 platelets when the normal range is 150-400). I was admitted to the ER for multiple days, and they gave a platelet transfusion and IVIG fluids, which has helped considerably. I also had to take steroids to suppress my immune system so that my platelets could increase.

Close
Aggravated very quickly; Everything went blank; She can't talk and when she tries to talk she feels like she has the hiccups where she can barely get the words to talk; when she has a hiccup her whole chest hurts; Hiccup; Numbness; Her whole right side would jerk uncontrollably; Weak; fever; itching; sore arm / burning; chills; A spontaneous report (United States) was received from a consumer who was also a 22-year-old female patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine who experienced sore arm/ burning (injection site pain), fever (pyrexia), chills, itching (injection site pruritus), numbness (injection site numbness), weak (asthenia), whole right side would jerk uncontrollably (myoclonus), everything went blank (loss of consciousness), couldn't talk and when she tried to talk she felt like she had the hiccups (aphasia), her whole chest hurt (chest discomfort), and quickly became aggravated (anger). The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. On 06 Jan 2021, the patient received her first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly in her right deltoid for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 06 Jan 2021, the patient experienced a sore arm, fever, chills, itching and burning. On 07 Jan 2021, on the site where the patient received the injection, she felt numbness and weak. Her whole right-side body would jerk uncontrollably. The patient went to two emergency rooms where they stated they did not know what was wrong and gave her a steroid injection that temporarily helped calm her down. On 08 Jan 2021, the patient stared at the door and everything went blank. She could not talk and when she tried to talk, she felt like she had the hiccups. She experienced her whole chest hurting when she had a hiccup. On 25 Jan 2021 and 26 Jan 2021, the patient saw two neurologists, who did testing. The patient's jerking was random, there were no triggers for it, and she did not know how to control or stop it. These adverse reactions made the patient become aggravated very quickly, which was not like her. On an unknown date, the patient stated it was the first day in the past month she had been able to talk all day. Treatment for the events included a steroid shot. Action taken with the second dose of mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not reported. The outcome for the events, sore arm/ burning, fever, chills, itching, numbness, weak, whole right side would jerk uncontrollably, everything went blank, couldn't talk and when she tried to talk she felt like she had the hiccups and her whole chest hurt, and quickly became aggravated, was not reported.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information which indicates a strong temporal association between the use of the product and the onset of the reported events a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Chills, fever, injection site pruritus and injection site pain are consistent with the known safety profile of mRNA-1273.

I monitored her blood pressure, which was low on the initial reading and then eventually came up to a reading of 89/60 with a pulse of 73 at the point that her symptoms began to subside. By approximately 45 minutes after the episode began, she reported feeling better and was able to stand and walk without symptoms. She went home at that time with a friend.

Fainted; Thirsty; Shaking; Look pale; Hypotension; Arm soreness; Nausea; CHILLS; Fever; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of SYNCOPE (Fainted) in a 22-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 008C21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. Concurrent medical conditions included Pollen allergy (environmental allergy) and Dust allergy (environmental allergy). Concomitant products included CETIRIZINE HYDROCHLORIDE (ZYRTEC [CETIRIZINE HYDROCHLORIDE]), FEXOFENADINE HYDROCHLORIDE (ALLEGRA) and CLARITHROMYCIN (CLARITIN [CLARITHROMYCIN]) for Allergy, MONTELUKAST for Asthma, COLECALCIFEROL (VITAMIN D [COLECALCIFEROL]) for Supplementation therapy. On 23-Apr-2021, the patient received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. On an unknown date, the patient received dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (unknown route) at an unspecified dose. On 24-Apr-2021, the patient experienced SYNCOPE (Fainted) (seriousness criterion medically significant), THIRST (Thirsty), TREMOR (Shaking), PALLOR (Look pale), HYPOTENSION (Hypotension), MYALGIA (Arm soreness), NAUSEA (Nausea), CHILLS (CHILLS) and PYREXIA (Fever). On 24-Apr-2021, SYNCOPE (Fainted), TREMOR (Shaking), PALLOR (Look pale) and HYPOTENSION (Hypotension) had resolved. At the time of the report, THIRST (Thirsty), MYALGIA (Arm soreness), NAUSEA (Nausea), CHILLS (CHILLS) and PYREXIA (Fever) outcome was unknown. The action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not applicable. The treatment medications included Tylenol (paracetamol) and Advil (Ibuprofen). Company comment: Based on the information provided which includes a temporal association between the use of mRNA-1273 vaccine and onset of the reported events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. I received my first dose of the Moderna vaccine on Tuesday, January 5th at 9:00 AM. I felt fine immediately following the vaccine but quickly felt worse throughout the day. I developed a fever of 101.4F with medicine, chills, muscle aches, fatigue, and general malaise. I know these are all common symptoms, so I didn't worry too much. However, my fever has persisted. I am guessing that pain in related to swollen lymph nodes. Friday, the pain in my armpit seemed to spread into my arm. Most of my armpit and the upper inside of my bicep is extremely tender to movement and touch. Today, I still have some tenderness in my arm and my fever is still present. Throughout this week, my fever has remained around 100F, even with Tylenol and ibuprofen. I contacted my PCP yesterday about my concern for my persistent fever and arm pain. They believe that because I tested positive for COVID-19 in October 2020, that I am reacting to the first dose of the vaccine as if I am receiving the second dose of the vaccine. They advised me to continue taking ibuprofen and Tylenol. I am worried that if I receive the second dose of the vaccine, I will be sick for longer.

I stay at my parents the night before work because their home is located much closer to work--my fiance and I live much farther away. I received the vaccination around 10AM Sunday morning. Sunday night I went to bed around 8:30PM and experienced severe chills throughout the night. I awoke around 12AM and got up to get a drink. I got a drink of water and checked my temperature, temp was 100.7. I felt yucky but not horrible. I walked back to my parents' room to tell them I would be staying home from work. As I got to their room and began to speak, I began to feel nauseous and weak and suddenly collapsed. My dad leaped up and helped me stand up so I could get to the restroom. I walked a few steps and then collapsed again and lost complete consciousness--I do not recall collapsing again or what happened shortly after. Per my dad, I was unresponsive, and he drug my limp body from his bedroom to the bathroom. My mom called 911. After several minutes, I regained consciousness and was leaning against my dad in the bathroom. I felt my fever break and was sweating profusely. EMS arrived at my home and checked vitals--everything was stable. I was A&O x3 and was able to drink water. I declined being transported to the hospital. I felt the loss of consciousness was likely due to dehydration or fever (although my fever really wasn't that high).

Immediately after the vaccine, I had redness around the injection site and a sore arm for about 2-3 days. I received the shot on a Tuesday, and by the weekend my arm felt fine. One week later (Monday 25th), I felt like I had a light fever. My temperature was 99.1F. Tuesday, my left arm where I received the injection was SO SUPER itchy. The area was also HOT to the touch even though the rest of my arm felt like a normal temperature. From Tuesday 26th through Wednesday 27th (time of reporting), I still have the big, red, hot bump at the injection site, and my fever fluctuates in between 99.1-100.4F. I contacted my doctor who believes it is most likely an allergic reaction to the vaccine. He has advised me to take benadryl and tylenol, and if I still have the fever tomorrow, he will test me for strep, flu, and COVID. I have not taken the benadryl and tylenol long enough to see if there is any sort of impact. I should also mention that I get tested weekly for COVID at work, and my test from Monday January 25 has come back as negative.

23 2021-01-29 fatigue, lethargy I received my second dose of the Moderna COVID vaccine at approx. 10:40 AM on Friday, January 29 at ... Read more
Close
I received my second dose of the Moderna COVID vaccine at approx. 10:40 AM on Friday, January 29 at clinic. By 12:00 PM, I noticed that I developed facial swelling, which was most significant around my eyes, and I felt lethargic. Between 12:00 PM and 2:00 PM, I developed hives on my neck, chest, stomach, and arms, which prompted me to take 1/2 of a dose of 25mg Benadryl. Nonetheless, the symptoms persisted and I began to experience dizziness and tightness in my throat around 4-5 PM, which was when I was advised by a nurse to go to the emergency room for treatment. I arrived at Hospital's Emergency Department around 6:00 PM and I was treated for "Possible Allergic Reaction Major." I received diphenhydrAMINE (BENADRYL) injection 50 mg, famotidine (PF) (PEPCID) injection 20 mg, methylPREDNISolone sodium succinate (PF) (SOLU-MEDROL) injection 125 mg, sodium chloride 0.9 % iv bolus, and acetaminophen (TYLENOL) tablet 650 mg. I was discharged after 10:00 PM and sent home with a prescription for predniSONE 20 mg and famotidine 20 mg. My facial swelling and hives have gone down but neither have completely resolved since being discharged. I am also experiencing full body aches and fatigue at this time (3 PM on Saturday, January 30).

Passed out twice; Pain in the injection site; Slight headache; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 24-year-old, female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced the events, passed out twice, pain in the injection site, and slight headache. The patient's medical history was not reported. No concomitant medications were reported. On 26 Dec 2020 at 1:58 pm, approximately three hours prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 026L2DA) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Briefly this is a 24-year-old with hypertrophic cardiomyopathy myopathy without obstruction presenting with fevers, chest tightness, and rigors after her 2nd COVID vaccine yesterday. She took Tylenol at home yesterday and on presentation this morning she already felt better. Her chest tightness was no longer present on admission and did not recur. EKG relatively unchanged from prior studies. She was febrile with an initial temperature of 39.3° C and tachycardic to 110. She was given 1 g of Tylenol and 15 mg Toradol as well as 2 L normal saline. Her temperature came down to 37.1 and her heart rate came down to 90. Subjectively she felt a lot better and was comfortably sitting upright in her bed. She drew a purple circle around the area and told me that if it goes outside the marked area or I feel any new symptoms, to go to the emergency room. Saturday morning on the 30th i woke up to my entire arm red and hot. I felt like I had a huge sunburn. I couldn?t put my sweatshirt on because it was so hot. The emergency room doctor told me I was fine and to keep taking the antibiotics that were given to me yesterday from my primary care doctor. After the emergency room I went to work and started to feel dizzy and nauseous. My hands became sweaty but the rest of my body was cold. I started having a butterfly feeling in my chest. My Apple Watch alerted me that my heart rate was over 100 bpm. That night before bed I had another low grade fever. On Sunday the 31st I noticed the red area was gone but instead it was a dark purple. I felt okay Sunday besides a rapid pulse. Monday February 1st I woke up out of a dead sleep sweating, butterfly feeling in my chest and dizzy. I tried to take my pulse while laying down but it was so fast I couldn?t keep up with it. I put my Apple Watch on which alerted me immediately that my pulse was 152 bpm. I slowly got up but then I passed out falling off of my bed. I couldn?t get any words out because my heart was beating so fast that I couldn?t breathe. I was sweating horribly and had a hard time walking. Had absolutely no strength in my left hand, my arm was purple/red, cold and numb. My arm felt like someone punched me repeatedly and gave me a dead arm. I called my primary doctors office and they were able to get me in that afternoon. All morning my pulse was spiking and then drastically dropping. About an hour and a half before I went to the doctor everything was fine. I was able to talk but still struggled with breathing while talking. The doctor ordered an EKG which came back clear. My pulse and blood pressure was also fine. The doctor told me she believed all of the symptoms I had were from the medication I take at night (doxazosin-to relax my muscles and help with sleep.) She also told me she believed some of it was my mental health issues taking over. She told me the cellulitis looked fine and sent me home. Later that day I felt exhausted and when I woke up from a nap, I had a fever of 100.5. Took Tylenol and it dropped to 99.5 but wouldn?t go any lower. February 2nd I woke up to a large red ring outside of the purple marker, numb finger tips and butterfly feeling in my chest. All day I received alerts that my pulse was falling and spiking. I sent my primary doctor an email and she told me she didn?t think it was cellulitis anymore, maybe a hematoma but she wasn?t sure. Since January 28th I still struggle everyday with the butterfly feeling in my chest, blurry vision, low grade temps, alerts of pulse, dizziness and breathing difficulties. My arm is always hot, my finger tips are numb and sometimes the strength in my hand is gone. The top of my arm is always a dark purple with red blotches and other times my entire arm is red and hot. When my pulse is very fast, I have a hard time talking, remembering what I was going to say and focusing. I?ve had multiple coworkers ask me if I?m okay because I?ll randomly stop talking and stare off and then I?m alerted that my pulse has either spiked or dropped drastically after spiking. My pulse is never consistent. It is always ranging from 57-155bpm. I realized at first I may have what they call ?COVID arm? but my symptoms haven?t gotten any better. No answers have been given to me or a diagnosis. The first diagnosis that they thought was cellulitis. Then it was ?in my head and behavioral.? Then it was a hematoma. Now it?s an ?I don?t know.? I have tried Benadryl for the itching, ice packs for the days that I?m swollen, Tylenol for the fevers and pain but I never have any relief.

Mild muscle soreness in right arm (injection site) beginning within an hour post-injection, noticeable with movement. Took 400mg of ibuprofen before bed. At 10.5 hours post-injection (middle of night), right arm soreness was moderate-to-severe at rest and severe, almost unbearable, with movement. Mild muscle soreness and joint pain were present throughout the body; joint pain (wrist, elbows, and knees) was an issue prior to injection and was exacerbated during the event. At 17.5 hours (following morning), muscle soreness was present in right arm alone and was mild at rest, moderate with movement. All other symptoms were gone. Experienced fatigue that afternoon (approx. 24 hours post-injection), treated effectively with a short nap and vitamin D (through sun exposure). On the 2nd full day post-injection, right arm muscle soreness is minimal with movement.

Passed out/passing out; Vertigo; Uncontrollable muscle twitching all over body; Dizziness/lightheadedness; Clammy hands/feet; Diarrhea; Gas; Rapid heart rate; Tingling in both feet/Tingling in bilateral feet; Liquid in both ears; Tiredness/fatigue; Nausea; Chills; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer, concerning a 24- year-old female who received Moderna's COVID vaccine and passed out and developed vertigo, dizziness, lightheadedness, uncontrollable muscle twitching, chills, clammy hands/feet/cold sweat, tingling in bilateral feet/paresthesia, fatigue ,nausea, liquid in the ears/ear discharge, diarrhea and gas/flatulence. The patient's past medical history was not provided. Products known to have been used by the patient, within two weeks prior to the event was reported as multivitamins (ascorbic acid, colecalciferaol, cyanocobalamin, pyridine hydrochloride, retinol palmitate, tocopherols mixed). On 04 March 2021 , prior to the onset of the event, the patient received first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot number:13A21A) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID 19 infection. On an unknown date after receiving the first dose of the vaccine the patient passed out which was considered as serious event (medically significant). The patient also experienced vertigo, dizziness, lightheadedness, uncontrollable muscle twitching, chills, clammy hands/feet ,tingling in bilateral feet, fatigue ,nausea, liquid in the ears, diarrhea, gas and tiredness. The patient reported that she passed out 30 seconds later after getting injection and it was not due to vasovagal reaction. As per patient, tingling started when she woke up early in the morning but in feet only. Treatment medications include dimenhydrinate and paracetamol. The patient took water and electrolytes for hydration. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to events was considered as unknown. The outcome of the events passed out and developed vertigo, dizziness, lightheadedness, uncontrollable muscle twitching, chills, clammy hands/feet/cold sweat, tingling in bilateral feet/paresthesia, fatigue ,nausea, liquid in the ears/ear discharge, diarrhea and gas/flatulence was considered as unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of these events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. The patient's past medical history included COVID-19 in October 2020. On 02-Apr-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 02-Apr-2021, the patient experienced BACK PAIN (Back pain). On 03-Apr-2021, the patient experienced SYNCOPE (Fainted) (seriousness criterion medically significant), SEIZURE (Had seizures twice) (seriousness criterion medically significant), INSOMNIA (couldn't sleep), MALAISE (Felt sick), FALL (Fell), MUSCULOSKELETAL STIFFNESS (Body went stiff), HEAD INJURY (Hit head on the wall) and VOMITING (Vomiting). At the time of the report, SYNCOPE (Fainted), SEIZURE (Had seizures twice), BACK PAIN (Back pain), INSOMNIA (couldn't sleep), MALAISE (Felt sick), FALL (Fell), MUSCULOSKELETAL STIFFNESS (Body went stiff), HEAD INJURY (Hit head on the wall) and VOMITING (Vomiting) outcome was unknown. The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Intramuscular) was unknown. For mRNA-1273 (Intramuscular), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments. Labs included Electrocardiogram: and Urine analysis, no test results provided. Treatment information not provided. Company comment: Very limited information regarding these events has been provided at this time. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. No Medical History information was reported. On 17-Apr-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 17-Apr-2021, the patient experienced SYNCOPE (Fainted), ANXIETY (Anxiety high), GENERAL PHYSICAL HEALTH DETERIORATION (general health bad), NAUSEA (Nausea) and PYREXIA (consistent low grade fever (100F to 100.4F)). On 28-Apr-2021, the patient experienced SKIN TIGHTNESS (face feels like it's tightening), DYSMENORRHOEA (painful menstrual period) and PALLOR (Pale as a ghost). At the time of the report, SYNCOPE (Fainted) had resolved, SOMNOLENCE (Cannot keep eyes open at work), SKIN TIGHTNESS (face feels like it's tightening), ANXIETY (Anxiety high), GENERAL PHYSICAL HEALTH DETERIORATION (general health bad), FAECES DISCOLOURED (diarrhea has been all kinds of colors(now orange)/black when she was taking Pepto-Bismol), FOREIGN BODY IN GASTROINTESTINAL TRACT (little stomach bug), DYSMENORRHOEA (painful menstrual period), PALLOR (Pale as a ghost), NAUSEA (Nausea) and PYREXIA (consistent low grade fever (100F to 100.4F)) outcome was unknown and DIARRHOEA (severe non-stop diarrhea since the day she got her vaccine) had not resolved. Not Provided The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown. No concomitant medications were reported. Treatment medications include Pepto-Bismol (bismuth subsalicylate) for diarrhea for 1.5 days (unknown dose/frequency). Patient waited out 20 minutes post-vaccination and then went to the bathroom. When she came out of bathroom she fainted, paramedics were summoned. Mother took patient to Emergency Room(ER) 20 April 2021, after taking her first to urgent care (who directed mother to take patient to the ER), ER sent her home saying it was just a little stomach bug, but no one else in the family got this "bug". Patient's last test for Covid-19 was on Monday (26-Apr-2021) and results came back negative on 28-Apr-2021. Vasovagal syncope (loss of consciousness) Tonic seizure (tensing and twitching of arms) Irregular heartbeat (per EKG) Extremely low blood pressure I received the vaccine at a public health pop-up, drive through clinic for first responders - I accessed the vaccine through my employer as a first responder. The vaccine was administered to my left arm without complication at approximately 1:00pm (my scheduled appointment). I proceeded to the area designated for patients to be observed after receiving the vaccine and was asked to wait 15 minutes. I recall getting to the observation area then telling my spouse I felt unwell - after the event he notified me that I told him I was about to pass out and asked him to get medical help. I lost consciousness approximately 5-10 minutes following the vaccine. My husband reported that after losing consciousness I seemed to have a minor seizure, as evidenced by my head jerking and my arms and fingers "tensing and curling up". I was sitting in the passenger seat of my car at this time, so I suffered no fall or fall related injury. Public health officials and EMT responded. They indicated to my spouse that I had experienced a vasovagal syncope episode and that I had "gone tonic"/ had a "tonic seizure". They took my blood pressure, which was very low (I don't recall exactly but it was 80 over something). They also took my blood sugar among other things that I do not recall. I was given oxygen and put into an ambulance. I was shaking, so they wrapped me in blankets. I believe they may have done an EKG and placed a blood pressure cuff while I was in the ambulance, but I do not recall any specifics about this. The EMT also drew my blood, placed an IV, and administered IV fluids while I was in the ambulance. I was taken by ambulance to the emergency department

On 1/16 the arm was still itchy and the lymph node was more enlarged. No neck or axillary nodes were enlarged. On 1/17 in the morning I woke up with a large red rash on my left deltoid. It was not itchy, but as the day went on was more red, raised, and warm. The node in my neck was causing some neck discomfort. I presented to Urgent Care and was treated for a local reaction. I was given a steroid cream to use on my arm and was told to take an OTC antihistamine. I have been using the cream for 2 days and so far the rash is resolving but is still visible. The node has not yet decreased in size.

Brain hemorrhage (inflammation, swelling); Dizziness; Difficulty with coordination; Difficulty with balance; Vision changes in left eye; Drift in left arm; Issues going through daily routine; Neurological symptoms; Was confused; Headaches; Very nauseous; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer, who was a 25-years-old, white female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced the events, very nauseous, neurological symptoms, headaches, dizziness, difficulty with coordination, difficulty with balance, vision changes in left eye, drift in left arm, issues going through daily routine, confusion, and brain bleed. The patient's medical history, as provided by the reporter, included gluten allergy. Products known to have been used by the patient, within two weeks prior to the event, included ethinylestradiol/ ferrous fumarate/ norethindrone acetate. On 06 Jan 2021 at 10:30am, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 06 Jan 2021, after receiving the vaccine, the patient became very nauseous through 08 Jan 2021. On 09 Jan 2021, the patient started having neurological symptoms. She started having headaches, dizziness, difficulty with coordination and balance, and vision changes in the left eye (not specified). She reported that she had a "drift" in the left arm and described it as "when you try to manipulate the arm, but it does not go where you want it to go". On 11 Jan 2021, the patient still had neurological symptoms, issues moving left arm, colliding with objects all day, and issues going through daily routine. On 12 Jan 2021, the patient was seen by a neurologist and magnetic resonance imagining (MRI) was scheduled. The MRI revealed inflammation, and brain bleed and swelling. The patient was sent to the emergency room and admitted on 19 Jan 2021. Treatment for the events included calcium carbonate for nausea, ibuprofen for headaches and diphenhydramine. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. The event, very nauseous, was considered resolved on 08 Jan 2021. The events, neurological symptoms, headaches, dizziness, difficulty with coordination, difficulty with balance, vision changes in left eye, drift in left arm and issues going through daily routine, confusion, and brain bleed were considered not resolved. Follow-up received on 23 Jan 2021 included patient details, medical history, lab tests, concomitant medications, hospitalization, and updated events.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a female patient, who experienced a non-serious unexpected event of dizziness, coordination abnormal, balance disorder, visual impairment, movement disorder, loss of personal independence in daily activities, and neurological symptom, and non-serious expected event of nausea, and headaches. The events of nausea occurred 1 day (same day) after first dose of mRNA-1273, lot # unknown. The event of neurological symptoms, dizziness, coordination abnormal, balance disorder, visual impairment, loss of personal independence in daily activities, and movement disorder occurred 3 days after first dose of mRNA-1273, lot # unknown. Treatment for the events included, Tums, nauseam, ibuprofen and Benadryl. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and onset of the events a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Rapid heartbeat; Shortness of breath; Pain at injection site; Chills; Fatigue; Fever; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 25 years-old, female patient who experienced rapid heartbeat/MedDRA PT: tachycardia, shortness of breath/MedDRA PT: dyspnoea, pain at injection site/MedDRA PT: vaccination site pain, chills/MedDRA PT: chills, fatigue/MedDRA PT: fatigue, and fever/MedDRA PT: pyrexia. The patient's medical history included anemia and low immune system. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. On 23 Jan 2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot # 025A202A) intramuscularly (injection site not provided) for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 23 Jan 2021, after receiving vaccination, the patient experienced pain at injection site, chills, fever, fatigue and shortness of breath. On 24 Jan 2021, the patient experienced rapid heartbeat. The patient was hospitalized and during hospitalization, heart rate was noted as 125 bpm which reduced down to 110 bpm. The patient was discharged on 25 Jan 2021. Following hospitalization, patient had ongoing fever and was advised to contact hospital for direction regarding readmission. Treatment included self-administered Tylenol, six times daily. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was unknown. The events chills and shortness of breath were considered resolved on 24 Jan 2021. The events pain at injection site, fatigue, and rapid heartbeat were considered resolved on an unknown date. The event fever was considered not resolved.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 25-year-old female who experienced serious expected events of tachycardia and dyspnea along with nonserious expected events of fever, chills, fatigue and vaccination site pain. The events occurred 1 day after the first dose of mRNA-1273. Treatment included Tylenol. Based on current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

At this time the symptoms felt similar to how I had felt during the worst of my previous Covid-19 symptoms, very weak and achy, headache was very bad, and felt very uncomfortable overall. Around 2:00 am on March 13 I woke up with a fever of 101.8. The previous symptoms had also gotten worse, I was having a hard time getting out of bed because things were very uncomfortable, I drank a lot of water and took some ibuprofen to combat the fever, about an hour after this the fever had come down to about 99.9 and I was able to fall asleep, but before taking the medication I couldn't have fallen asleep because of the discomfort of the aches, chills, and fever. Throughout the following day I was unable to complete many of my day to day activities without taking a daytime cold and flu medication. With the medication I still felt sick but was able to walk around and complete some simple household chores, this carried through into the evening, when the medication wore off the chills and aches and headache were much worse and I still had a fever around 99-100. That night I was able to sleep with the cold and flu medication taken right before bed. Upon waking up the next morning (March 14) I still had some congestion, headache, and general discomfort but the worst of the aches were gone and I no longer had a fever, these symptoms continued to diminish throughout the day. On March 15 and March 16th I have had a slight lingering congestion headache, this also feels really similar to the lingering headache I had upon recovering from Covid-19. It is not debilitating and is continuing to improve. Otherwise I am feeling healthy again and have been able to complete my usual activities and even exercise. Overall the symptoms felt like a couple days of having Covid-19 again, but recovery was much faster, and it was definitely worth receiving that first dose of the vaccine and getting started with the process of doing my part to reduce community spread.

One week after vaccine, injection site became extremely swollen (approx. 2"x3" induration), burning hot to the touch, tender & itchy, arm became numb. General malaise, low grade fever. Site reaction spread down arm, went to urgent care & was told it may be cellulitis & was given antibiotics & told to go to ER if it continued to spread. Reaction continued to spread, arm/hand numbness & general feeling of illness, slight fever continued for approx. 2 weeks following vaccine. Site reaction fully subsided visually by 1/26 (began 1/15). Allergist suggested it was severe immune reaction to vaccine. Felt generally unwell for approx. 5 weeks following vaccine. Was told I should not get second dose or any covid/flu vaccines in the future. I have history of poor reaction to vaccines/site reactions.

I continued to feel light headed and extremely tired through arriving at the hospital via ambulance around 10:30am. These symptoms gradually subsided throughout the afternoon leaving me with light headedness only when walking or moving around. While at the hospital they did an EKG which showed inverted T waves (from what I remember of the PA's description) and so admitted me for observation and performed an echo which came back normal. I was discharged around 10pm on the same night.

25 2021-05-10 headache, sweating Approximately 10 minutes after the patient got her second moderna vaccine she became faint and dizzy... Read more
Close
Approximately 10 minutes after the patient got her second moderna vaccine she became faint and dizzy. The patient was sitting at the time. A law enforcement officer witnessed her becoming faint and ran over to attend her. I was called over to assess her as well. The law enforcement officer called EMS. The patient stated that she felt faint, dizzy, she said she had a headache, blurry vision, and was nauseous. The patient appeared sweaty and she appeared to loose consciousness briefly twice. She did not show any signs of redness, rash, or swelling. After sitting for a few minutes, and before EMS arrived, the patient said she was improving. She did not lose consciousness anymore but she still had a headache, nausea, and blurry vision. When EMS arrived they recommended that she get checked out at the emergency room, but the patient refused stating that she did not want to go to the hospital and that she was feeling better. The patient called her parents and they came and picked her up.
